CTA1 mRNA induction (Fig. 3A)

Experiment was performed on 2020/03/25-27, see here for experimental methods. Briefly, C. glabrata cells were grown to mid-log phase (OD~0.5), washed and treated with either SC media (mock), 0mM Pi (no Pi) or 10 mM H2O2 for 45 minutes. RNA was extracted and qRT-PCR was performed with ACT1 used as a reference gene and the mock treated sample as the reference sample. The following dataset was extracted from the above spreadsheet.

rna <- read_tsv("input/CTA1-mRNA-qPCR/20200327-CTA1-mRNA-Ct.txt") %>% 
  mutate(Treatment = fct_recode(Treatment, 
                                H2O2 = "10mM H2O2", 
                                `-Pi` = "no Pi", 
                                Mock = "untreated"))

Calculate ∆∆Ct. Because the dilution amount is the same across all samples, we don’t have to make any adjustments. TRUE

rna.ddCt <- rna.dCt %>% 
  # calculate mean dCt for the reference sample
  filter(Treatment == "Mock") %>% 
  group_by(Name, Target) %>% 
  summarize(refT = mean(dCt), .groups = "drop") %>% 
  right_join(rna.dCt) %>% 
  mutate(ddCt = dCt - refT, FC = 2^-ddCt) %>% 
  select(-refT)

Joining, by = c("Name", "Target")

Visualize fold changes relative to the mock treated sample and normalized by ACT1. Using CTA1 primer set A. Overall pattern is highly consistent. Primer set C data contains one outlier that is most likely due to experimental mistakes – one -Pi sample showed >400 fold induction

treat_color <- c(`H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub>` = "#E69138", `-Pi` = "#9900FF", Mock = "#666666")
